Nigerian-born British boxer, Anthony Joshua, on Saturday, visited popular Lagos slum, Makoko. AJ, as he is popularly called visited the Slum2School initiative located in Makoko, where he spent time with the children. From videos shared on the verified Instagram page of the initiative, he even shared some boxing tips with the children. Joshua won the unified world heavyweight champion, having held the World Boxing Association, International Boxing Federation and World Boxing Organization titles between 2016 and 2019. He, however, lost all titles to Mexican, Andy Ruiz in June.  